  "root_text": {
    "iti61:0.1": "Itivuttaka 61 ",
    "iti61:0.2": "Tikanipāta ",
    "iti61:0.3": "Dutiyavagga ",
    "iti61:0.4": "Cakkhusutta ",
    "iti61:1.1": "Vuttañhetaṁ bhagavatā vuttamarahatāti me sutaṁ: ",
    "iti61:2.1": "“Tīṇimāni, bhikkhave, cakkhūni. ",
    "iti61:2.2": "Katamāni tīṇi? ",
    "iti61:2.3": "Maṁsacakkhu, dibbacakkhu, paññācakkhu—",
    "iti61:2.4": "imāni kho, bhikkhave, tīṇi cakkhūnī”ti. ",
    "iti61:2.5": "Etamatthaṁ bhagavā avoca. ",
    "iti61:2.6": "Tatthetaṁ iti vuccati: ",
    "iti61:3.1": "“Maṁsacakkhu dibbacakkhu, ",
    "iti61:3.2": "paññācakkhu anuttaraṁ; ",
    "iti61:3.3": "Etāni tīṇi cakkhūni, ",
    "iti61:3.4": "akkhāsi purisuttamo. ",
    "iti61:4.1": "Maṁsacakkhussa uppādo, ",
    "iti61:4.2": "maggo dibbassa cakkhuno; ",
    "iti61:4.3": "Yato ñāṇaṁ udapādi, ",
    "iti61:4.4": "paññācakkhu anuttaraṁ; ",
    "iti61:4.5": "Yassa cakkhussa paṭilābhā, ",
    "iti61:4.6": "sabbadukkhā pamuccatī”ti. ",
    "iti61:5.1": "Ayampi attho vutto bhagavatā, iti me sutanti. ",
    "iti61:5.2": "Dutiyaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "iti61:0.1": "So It Was Said 61 ",
    "iti61:0.2": "The Book of the Threes ",
    "iti61:0.3": "Chapter Two ",
    "iti61:0.4": "The Eye ",
    "iti61:1.1": "This was said by the Buddha, the Perfected One: that is what I heard. ",
    "iti61:2.1": "“Mendicants, there are these three eyes. ",
    "iti61:2.2": "What three? ",
    "iti61:2.3": "The eye of the flesh, the eye of clairvoyance, and the eye of wisdom. ",
    "iti61:2.4": "These are the three eyes.” ",
    "iti61:2.5": "The Buddha spoke this matter. ",
    "iti61:2.6": "On this it is said: ",
    "iti61:3.1": "“The eye of flesh, the clairvoyant eye, ",
    "iti61:3.2": "the supreme eye of wisdom: ",
    "iti61:3.3": "these three eyes ",
    "iti61:3.4": "were taught by the supreme person. ",
    "iti61:4.1": "The arising of the eye of flesh ",
    "iti61:4.2": "is the path to the clairvoyant eye. ",
    "iti61:4.3": "When knowledge arises—",
    "iti61:4.4": "the supreme eye of wisdom—",
    "iti61:4.5": "one who gains that eye ",
    "iti61:4.6": "is released from all suffering.” ",
    "iti61:5.1": "This too is a matter that was spoken by the Blessed One: that is what I heard. "
  },
